```February 27th, University Acceptance```

Finally, the tuition was fully paid, and his housing and school situations have been handled by his superior [and his assistant]. He was elated that he could finally get down to business, and possibly run into some of the demons he met on the outskirts previously...Playing a college kid again is going to be quite an experience...

Lysander confidently walks into his new room, taking time to soak in the atmosphere around him. For a supposed demon infested university, the dorms were pretty high quality, spacious, no roommates...And the amount of amenities offered to this school, there must be some wealthy characters who attend this college...Which also meant that there could be aristocratic and high rank demons "attending" as well. 

No matter, he is nothing more than an informant for now. 

First, to rearrange this dorm room for comfort...And to hide his equipment. 

```Monologue 1: END```

mi, Kou Mukami, Azusa Mukami [Out of Commission]...Please get back to me about this name as well.

I will continue my quest for information, hoping I can get something out of "Rosenfeld" soon. But I am minding my pace, I can't be too hasty in my questioning or they will suspect me. I might be suspicious just from my conduct in the chatroom already;;; This whole trying to sound like a college kid thing is fucking hard! I've only been outta college for...8? 9 years? 

Anyway, I'll end this here. Remember, DO NOT contact me back. Hoping this gets to you safely. 

-The Hawk`  

```Telecom 1: END```

``` March 7th, After the Call with Tamura``` 

Boss~

Still alive! For starters, the students here are quite strange. I've been keeping in contact with a human student: Michi Tamura. They seem to be heavily involved with some of the demons in the school. I have more suspicions that lead me to believe that the humans at this university willingly get into..." entanglements " with demons. I guess this shouldn't come as a surprise considering these creatures are good at deception. Maybe I should get into one in order to seem less suspicious? I'll update you on this matter later. 

Tonight I will be in close proximity to a possible demon royal...Alrick Rosenfeld. I don't think anything major will happen, however,  please advise. I would like to request more equipment if possible. 

``` Lysander sends out a requisition form for the following: Experimental demon perfumes, tranquilizers, demon restraints, silver, and temporary repellents.``` 

I will keep in touch~ 

- The Hawk

``` Telecom 2: END```

Lys: ...Understood, sir. 

Comm: I like you, okay. I like you a lot. Otherwise, this demon research bullshit you got goin' on, I wouldn't have allowed it if I didn't. I don't like yelling at you...

Lys: Mhm...

Comm: But you gatta do _more_. You know what I'm sayin'? 

Lys: Yeah. 

Comm: Your morals, your pride, your dignity. Out the door. **You** signed up for this life. **Do it.**

Lys: Yes, sir...

Comm: One more thing; I got reports on top of the "animal attacks" and serial murders; there was a wolf hybrid, going by the name "Amina" hospitalized for critical injuries. Comatose. Along with this, sightings of an individual who _was_ with her at a festival days prior. Do you know of this? Can you confirm?

Lys: `Shit...`  I...Saw _something_ that was slightly strange, but I can't confirm that it was "Amina' or this said, individual. I've never seen what Amina looks like...

Comm: God. Did you know _anything_? This is your fucking job, isn't it?!  `A heavy sigh and the creaking of a chair could be heard over the phone.`  
...Okay. Just--Do as I said. Be more proactive, and jump into the water. Stop being shy about it, I _know_ you can do more. And for fuck's sake, do not forget to report back with any findings. Tell us every. Single. Detail. **Every detail.** That is all, Detective. 

Lys: ...Yes, sir...

``` CALL END```

Sitting back in his computer chair, Lysander places his phone down on the desk...Slumping his chin onto his palm with a somber stare at a blank monitor screen. In his thoughts, he repeats his Commander's words...Over and over. Analyzing what he should do differently...How he should _get more involved_...

He sighs, glancing over to the demon perfume he created sitting on the dresser...

"..."

"..."

"..."

He stands to his feet, the hunter's eyes never leaving the bottle of liquid as he steps closer to it...Finally, laying a hand on it, the other hand reaches for the hidden blade that hugs the back of his thigh. 

"..."

"..."

"..."

The index of Lysander's finger slides back and forth on the spine of the blade as he contemplates...Eyesight was still focused on the bottle...

"..." 

"..." 

"..." 

The hunter slowly glides the hidden blade out of its holster, now holding it in front of his face, blankly staring at his reflection in the pristine silver. Closing his eyes and furrowing his brows, Lysander lets out one last sigh...Then picks up the perfume, putting the blade on the dresser in its place. 

He knew this was stupid...

He knew this was foolish...

But for now..._He was not a hunter. He was a student at Ryoutei University...Just like everyone else..._ 

``` END```

``` They both continued to wind each other up, eventually ending in Lys getting pinned against the wall in the showers. Aoi may or may not have had a nibble, all while taunting the hunter. Then he left. The end.```

```Upon Lysander leaning over, Noah simply didn't budge as he blinked a couple times.```

`too close...`

```One would expect that he would lean back, but no- he just pressed his pointer finger on Lys' forhead and pushed him back```

**"Sort of and no"**

```He said with his now rosey cheeks puffing```

@LYSANDER DAYTONA RUIZ

``` Once again, the Pink-haired man's break in his usual shy, reserved nature...Or what the Hunter thought Noah was left him stunned. He was seeing all sides of Noah today...After Noah's departure, he sat on the ice cream parlor bench moments later, still digesting what he just heard...What he saw. Noah's expression reminded him of that time when he was sure he cornered Alrick in the classroom...Like a wild animal who just got shot.``` 

"...Pff..."

``` The Hunter covers his eyes, and he giggles silently to himself as he stares down at the tacky table pattern. He hoped he didn't look like a madman, quietly smiling to himself. But for this moment, he couldn't help it, it was too amusing. Alrick Rosenfeld...Then Noah Lafayette...They were both in so much denial. Tortured children of the darkness are forced to think they are sophisticated. This...This tasted better than any ice cream. He had to think of a way to get Noah to speak to him again...Or maybe he'll come back, who knows. But for now, he'll give the poor puppy his space...For now.``` 

_Keep making this interesting, Noah. Alrick. Maybe if you two are good boys, one day, I might let you act on those desires...Just because I like you...Maybe~_

``` Before leaving the shop, he finishes off the ice cream, eagerly watching people pass back and forth...Planning...``` 

@NOAH LAFAYETTE 


``` END ```

Alrick's cold words didn't fit his halfhearted actions, it amused the hunter to his core...Watching not only a demon but a _royal_ demon cringe and crumble under the influence. If this were any other setting, Lysander would push him further, he wondered what the boy's crying face would look like...Would he beg? Sob? Lash out like a cornered animal? His eyes were fixated on the man's red eyes till his figure disappeared from behind the classroom door.    

His hurried footsteps echoed through the quiet hallways, then came to an abrupt stop...Followed by a muffled thud. Lysander put a hand over his lips...A heinous grin painted his face followed by a giddy snicker. _He's perfect. Even those of the elite can't fight their own nature...His imperious little attitude...His drop-dead gorgeous looks...This is an opportunity that would be criminal to pass up. Did his wife tame him? First Lady, I get it now. I understand why you tied him down..._ 

"Alrick Rosenfeld...Do you bend...Or do you break...?" Lysander mumbles through his breath as he quietly exits the classroom.  

``` END ```

Hmm~? Am I really that scary, Tamura-san~?

`He teases, leaning in closer to Tama`

`After Lysander leves, Tama stands up, gathering his things. Putting the manga back on the shelf where it belonged because, let’s face it, he’s probably read it already. Afterwards he leaves and goes back to his dorm.`

`[End]`

The nurse instructs Lysander no further, prompting the man to silently leave the clinic. Once he was out of sight, his once expression of sorrowed anxiety contorts back to distant anger. A sigh of frustration escapes his lips, as he observed the damage done to his clothes and body...Bruised, bitten, and annoyed; he heads back to his dorm room to clean himself off. 

*This kid is more trouble than I expected...*

@NOAH LAFAYETTE 

```END```
